	<h1>ICADoA - Intelligent Chatbot for Anxiety and Depression</h1>
<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>ICADoA is an intelligent chatbot designed to provide support and resources for individuals struggling with anxiety and depression. The chatbot uses natural language processing and sentiment analysis to understand user inputs and provide personalized responses.</p>

<h2>Features</h2>
<ul>
	<li>Generates responses using GPT-2 language model</li>
	<li>Classifies sentiment of user messages using BERT-based model</li>
	<li>Stores chat history in SQLite database</li>
	<li>Provides conversational flows for smoother interactions</li>
</ul>

<h2>Installation and Setup</h2>
<p>Follow the instructions below to install and set up ICADoA:</p>

<ol>
	<li>Clone this repository to your local machine</li>
	<li>Ensure you have Python 3.x installed on your machine</li>
	<li>Create a virtual environment for ICADoA by running <code>python3 -m venv icadoa_env</code></li>
	<li>Activate the virtual environment by running <code>source icadoa_env/bin/activate</code> on Unix-based systems or <code>icadoa_env\Scripts\activate</code> on Windows</li>
	<li>Install the required packages by running <code>pip install -r requirements.txt</code></li>
	<li>Run the chatbot by running <code>python main.py</code></li>
	<li>Enter your message and interact with the chatbot in the console</li>
</ol>

<h2>Usage</h2>
<p>To use the chatbot, simply type your message in the console and press Enter. The chatbot will process your message and generate a response based on its analysis of your sentiment and the context of the conversation.</p>

<p>You can exit the chatbot at any time by typing "exit" in the console.</p>

<h2>Contributing</h2>
<p>If you would like to contribute to the development of ICADoA, please fork this repository and create a pull request with your changes.</p>

